  serverChannel.bind(new InetSocketAddress(InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), 0));\n            int port = ((InetSocketAddress) serverChannel.getLocalAddress()).getPort();\n            Future<byte[]> serverResult = executor.submit(\n                    () -> runPskSocketServer(serverContext, serverChannel, cipherSuite));\n\n            try (SocketChannel clientChannel = SocketChannel.open(\n                         new InetSocketAddress(InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), port));\n                    SSLSocket clientSocket = (SSLSocket) clientContext.getSocketFactory()\n                            .createSocket(clientChannel.socket(), \"localhost\", port, true)) {\n                clientSocket.setEnabledProtocols(new String[] {PROTOCOL});\n                clientSocket.setEnabledCipherSuites(new String[] {cipherSuite});\n                clientSocket.startHandshake();\n                OutputStream output = clientSocket.getOutputStream();\n                output.write(7);\n                output.flush();\n                assertEquals(11, clientSocket.getInputStream().read());\n            }\n            assertArrayEquals(new byte[] {7}, serverResult.get(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS));\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] runPskSocketServer(SSLServerSocket serverSocket) throws Exception {\n        try (SSLSocket server = (SSLSocket) serverSocket.accept()) {\n            server.startHandshake();\n            InputStream input = server.getInputStream();\n            int received = input.read();\n            OutputStream output = server.getOutputStream();\n            output.write(11);\n            output.flush();\n            return new byte[] {(byte) received};\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] runPskSocketServer(SSLContext serverContext,\n            ServerSocketChannel serverChannel, String cipherSuite) throws Exception {\n        try (SocketChannel acceptedChannel = serverChannel.accept();\n                SSLSocket server = (SSLSocket) serverContext.getSocketFactory().createSocket(\n                        acceptedChannel.socket(), \"localhost\", acceptedChannel.socket().getPort(), true)) {\n            server.setUseClientMode(false);\n            server.setEnabledProtocols(new String[] {PROTOCOL});\n            server.setEnabledCipherSuites(new String[] {cipherSuite});\n            server.startHandshake();\n            InputStream input = server.getInputStream();\n            int received = input.read();\n            OutputStream output = server.getOutputStream();\n            output.write(11);\n            output.flush();\n            return new byte[] {(byte) received};\n        }\n    }\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Configuring JVM access**\n\nI’m looking into normal JVM settings with java.net. First, when `setAccessible` fails due to `sun.nio.ch` not being open, I need to consider a fallback to `Socket.impl`, which might return an invalid state. To address this, I might need to add the `--add-opens sun.nio.ch` option to allow the channel path. I'll also check if there are any restrictions in the reflection config, and edit that as needed.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04a121b9430b3ca90169f2a7af1c748194b7449353cab80f9a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8qe90f5x_e8yJzoddGvnB37BzubBUYX9P4i9-L-ygjPKVwLks2lf-98BDg4b4em_0NJofHnVyxkgnfrFGeSAZVYDdiGEAGCpvsVKyUZLHBoYq327IhFvzFMxdkcLg1Zd2228oMZOAX8C-gDFUJCuyo45xnZ9MdmbfznLCI27Wuo_ALpO2XtBQusij_r_Z_xNRv_OhhmdX706o6W1c15TtZX6xoUm9fPm6k2CjqRJHCr3fYvb3sxsyfxdKu-07TPqG5v9QtOiXJBH7EqeMToCpd6QyMrirASZ56PGwUddCdomIayMIOuWvo-xRoWQvOrkMlj4j0TnKC9y1Me1Gd7xQVGbf8yQAojbZIe8_D-UqMsbZcYjxQ8B_umuExzjmiI1xrH4dw1bmh79aAtvc1jZ9d2On8yZaWDbV-xtz1ZyuzcbzM53bXbLBP6o_yDOZVYUcI3iN2p2IQI8CxxQWGxwP5Mnw4xeZ53yBw8kOY1pG-pKq_jPuPXz3RuBnghSydhcgwaY0TCaqRKL3ArVqI3Pn2VCkpUfC_mD6l7gyojCBU9ACl8OYycEgWhK7UDMKquy6sZaF0KGHXhgkUUoYWzMedGj0kAmNQB_cRcLFioIVK7Ah3vyHMpkkVi8K3wqZNN1W6w-6lO_Ir_Wbt7dgnERNF-4R5nOJCcD2tvcI7NqkkD0qA5H3g4MZQ4MloaxWlrSDU9m7tWR_mW5g7RBiYxvH4o6GU5OukVoBUlafEGO-M5xpt8gM2b-CrtgAz5Nogczq2JZ7yfWM3xDyv5j7R67QYTD62pZEVVgoot8W7yk278_XJdStzzxS9GW8_4SwWOYbVXuRNBX8XOBxb2vPTdJYgKA_cwwml_cwOrmDxqlZA8JuAyA1E5iyk4sMsye0ubqHsjByKbWtoB6cbbKikirIx55RNXY2X06gdVidbDY1uN0neLfJqH16WrJVdhMgXbyLMkHhd2QhuzAmugJiI1ucKvUFV5vWL74BkqTbrsy1lClX59o-7aM0ybz2XWDabOWloibsyBDhmTAj37l92pxWBK5ybQ0cgxsnyWfvQMAnfOcNMsI26CaX39Thq9yTXMVdbh7wiQpiT_Dz04X1Qb23DlI1JW9pbdwOHIO0PlWsawIar5gVn70Ei33gl3KvugGLIjrNHPN7-DaynE2cnMTE_VjXqhj-x7SZoSC2AFLE6cxUfp2RmeNkkOBubYgI6HkM1pEnMxWBP2br0RjSCwog8yzlqqAsFKZd7rWtG_UEoZ5X3oJboFZ_I5cuIrrETaQyxRddlzIHCsk4ljTop4AbGbTKTJFrts