6566Gx0h3_RGBBws1bBQRrjx8Sa-nuR5YuPvJyY-P4O4zj22MD\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring JVM access**\\n\\nI’m looking into normal JVM settings with java.net. First, when `setAccessible` fails due to `sun.nio.ch` not being open, I need to consider a fallback to `Socket.impl`, which might return an invalid state. To address this, I might need to add the `--add-opens sun.nio.ch` option to allow the channel path. I'll also check if there are any restrictions in the reflection config, and edit that as needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GEm6u9E1iVoQrCZukXULgpuv|fc_04a121b9430b3ca90169f2a7bd00088194b4aeec8eff96a3e4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.conscrypt/conscrypt-openjdk-uber/1.4.0/src/test/java/org_conscrypt/conscrypt_openjdk_uber/DuckTypedPSKKeyManagerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.net.InetAddress;\nimport java.net.Socket;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\n", "newText": "import java.net.InetAddress;\nimport java.net.InetSocketAddress;\nimport java.net.Socket;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\nimport java.nio.channels.ServerSocketChannel;\nimport java.nio.channels.SocketChannel;\n"}, {"oldText": "import javax.net.ssl.SSLServerSocket;\nimport javax.net.ssl.SSLSession;\n", "newText": "import javax.net.ssl.SSLSession;\n"}, {"oldText": "        try (SSLServerSocket serverSocket = (SSLServerSocket) serverContext.getServerSocketFactory()\n                .createServerSocket(0, 1, InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress())) {\n            serverSocket.setEnabledProtocols(new String[] {PROTOCOL});\n            serverSocket.setEnabledCipherSuites(new String[] {cipherSuite});\n            Future<byte[]> serverResult = executor.submit(() -> runPskSocketServer(serverSocket));\n\n            try (SSLSocket clientSocket = (SSLSocket) clientContext.getSocketFactory()\n                    .createSocket(InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), serverSocket.getLocalPort())) {\n                clientSocket.setEnabledProtocols(new String[] {PROTOCOL});\n                clientSocket.setEnabledCipherSuites(new String[] {cipherSuite});\n                clientSocket.startHandshake();\n                OutputStream output = clientSocket.getOutputStream();\n                output.write(7);\n                output.flush();\n                assertEquals(11, clientSocket.getInputStream().read());\n            }\n            assertArrayEquals(new byte[] {7}, serverResult.get(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS));\n", "newText": "        try (ServerSocketChannel serverChannel = ServerSocketChannel.open()) {\n            serverChannel.bind(new InetSocketAddress(InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), 0));\n            int port = ((InetSocketAddress) serverChannel.getLocalAddress()).getPort();\n            Future<byte[]> serverResult = executor.submit(\n                    () -> runPskSocketServer(serverContext, serverChannel, cipherSuite));\n\n            try (SocketChannel clientChannel = SocketChannel.open(\n                         new InetSocketAddress(InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), port));\n                    SSLSocket clientSocket = (SSLSocket) clientContext.getSocketFactory()\n                            .createSocket(clientChannel.socket(), \"localhost\", port, true)) {\n                clientSocket.setEnabledProtocols(new String[] {PROTOCOL});\n                clientSocket.setEnabledCipherSuites(new String[] {cipherSuite});\n                clientSocket.startHandshake();\n                OutputStream output = clientSocket.getOutputStream();\n                output.write(7);\n                output.flush();\n                assertEquals(11, clientSocket.getInputStream().read());\n            }\n            assertArrayEquals(new byte[] {7}, serverResult.get(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS));\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static byte[] runPskSocketServer(SSLServerSocket serverSocket) throws Exception {\n        try (SSLSocket server = (SSLSocket) serverSocket.accept()) {\n            server.startHandshake();\n            Inpu